text.tspan: Child mortality rate in boys and girls per 1,000 live births, 2015
Child mortality rate in boys versus rate in girls. Under-five mortality rate, is the probability per 1,000 that a newborn
baby will die before reaching age five, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year. Also shown is
the parity line, along which mortality rates in boys and girls are equal.
Child mortality rate of girls (per 1,000 births)
